      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>A rectangular <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> shaft</rs>, broken in two (total <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">1.27</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.50</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.40</measure>), with panels within moulded edges on three sides.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> within the central panel.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>Av. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.04</measure>, ll.9-10, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.03</measure>; irregular; <foreign lang="grc">Ε</foreign> lunate and square; ligature, <foreign lang="grc">ΝΗ</foreign> in l.2</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0468" notAfter="0600">Late fifth/sixth century</date> (language).</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
		<lg met="dactylic hexameter">
		<lb n="1"/>
		<l><g type="cross"/> <w lemma="πατρίς">Πατρὶς</w>
		<lb n="2"/><persName key="Ioannes3" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Ἰωάννης">Ἰωάν<hi rend="ligature">νη</hi>ν</name></persName>
		<lb n="3"/><w lemma="πρωτόθρονος">πρωτόθρο
		<lb n="4" type="worddiv"/>νον</w> <w lemma="ἀνήρ">ἀνέρα</w>
		<lb n="5"/><rs type="subject" key="boule"><w lemma="βουλή">βουλῆς</w></rs></l>
		<lb n="6"/>
		<l><w lemma="ἵστημι">στῆσεν</w>
		<lb n="7"/><w lemma="δέχομαι">δεξαμένη</w>
		<lb n="8"/><w lemma="θρεπτήριος">θρεπτήρια</w>
		<lb n="9"/><w lemma="πολλάκις">πολλάκι</w>
		<lb n="10"/><w lemma="πολύς">πολλά</w>.</l>
		</lg>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab>The fatherland set up <supplied reason="subaudible">this statue of</supplied> Ioannes, who has the first seat in the Council, having often received from him many repayments for his rearing.</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="V.51">V.51</xref> following.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p>Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Temple/Church</rs>: re-used face downwards as a step at the north-west corner of the Bema.</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation">Unknown; <seg cert="low"><rs key="Boul" type="monuList">Bouleuterion</rs></seg>.</rs>. Last recorded location: <rs type="lastLocation">Temple-Church.</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

      <div type="history" n="record">
        <head>History of Recording</head>
        <p>Excavated by the NYU expedition in 1965 (<rs type="invNo">65.511</rs>).</p>
      </div>

